<br>
The problem as I see it is that we have a few who have extremely strong opinions, (namely, Wyrdlan, Ven, Fedral).  Yes, I'm naming names, and if you didn't want to be named, too bad.  All your opinions, of course, are valid.  But everyone is miscommunicating and reading words wrong, therefore jumping to conclusions because we may not be stating things as clear as we can.  I personally know where most people are coming from with their points, but I don't think many others do.  <br>
<br>
Stop from ignoring what others are saying and LISTEN.  By listening, and I mean not only the words, but understanding WHAT they mean.  I hate to be 'lecturing' you guys on it, although every single one of us need to at least consider what someone else is saying instead of disagreeing all the time and saying &quot;but that's wrong, you should do it MY way.&quot;  There is NO ONE WAY.  If they're wrong, tell them nicely why and for what reason and try to rationalize with them until they see it too.  Just don't go around thinking we all have to abide by your way.  STOP being STUBBORN.<br>
<br>
Running away and conceding from a certain issue isn't the answer either.  It does nothing to help when you leave just because the majority are siding with the ones that are opposing your viewpoint.  Even then, it might not the viewpoint we don't agree with, but the way in which the situation is being handled.  Nor does it help the guild when all you want is to help in the first place, and you end up leaving.  I see that as the easy way out, you are leaving so as to not have to deal with the mess that has been made.  GO BACK AND FIX IT!  If you love the guild so much, why leave?  Why not help make it better and learn from what has gone so terribly wrong?  What's that very cliche saying?  If at first you don't succeed....I believe everyone knows how it ends.<br>
<br>
*gets off the soapbox*<br>
<br>
In all that I've said...I hope none of you take it the wrong way.  I'm all for working things out, and the recent events have even driven me off the deep end or close to it.<br>
<br>
As a last note, I'm sorry about you losing your job Zapo, and for anyone out there who has also recently lost their jobs.  I wish you luck in finding a new and better one soon.  Take care of yourselves and please try not to stress out too much.  This, after all, is a GAME.<br>
<br>
-Luwelyn Mathunnos<br>
